HEADWORD: Infrigidate
<hw>In*frig"i*date</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>infrigidatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>infrigidare</ets> to chill. See
1st <er>In-</er>, and <er>Frigid</er>.]</ety> <def>To chill; to make
cold; to cool.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
